>(OH + CF<inf>3</inf>CFHOCF<inf>3</inf>) = (1.4 ± 0.3) × 10 -15 cm3 molecule-1 s-1. The atmospheric lifetime of CF<inf>3</inf>CFHOCF<inf>3</inf> is estimated to be 40 years. The IR spectrum of CF<inf>3</inf>CFHOCF<inf>3</inf> was measured and used to estimate a global warming potential (relative to CO<inf>2</inf>, 100 year time horizon) for CF<inf>3</inf>CFHOCF<inf>3</inf> of 4500. Results are discussed with respect to the previous literature data. Copyright 2002 by the American Geophysical Union.","Atmospheric lifetime; Global warming potential; OH radical reaction","Atmospheric chemistry; Climatology; Global warming; Oxidation; Smoke; atmospheric chemistry; chemical reaction; FTIR spectroscopy; global warming; hydroxyl radical; life cycle; organic compound; oxidation; smog",,,,,,"Atkinson, R., Baulch, D.L., Cox, R.A., Hampson Jr., R.F., Kerr, J.A., Rossi, M.J., Troe, J., Evaluated kinetic, photochemical and heterogeneous data for atmospheric chemistry: Supplement V (1997) J. Phys. Chem. Ref. Data., 26, pp. 521-1011; DeMore, W.B., Sander, S.P., Golden, D.M., Hampson, R.F., Kurylo, M.J., Howard, C.J., Ravishankara, A.R., Molina, M.J., (1997) Chemical Kinetics and Photochemical Data for Use in Stratospheric Modeling, , Publ. 97-4, Jet Propulsion Laboratory, Pasadena, Calif; Dibble, T.S., Francisco, J.S., Determination of the heats of formation of FC(O)C and FC(O)OH (1994) J. Phys. Chem., 98, pp. 11,694-11,696; Finlayson-Pitts, B.J., Pitts, J.N., (1999) Chemistry of the Upper and Lower Atmosphere: Theory, Experiments and Applications, , Academic, San Diego, Calif; Good, D.A., Francisco, J.S., Bond dissociation energies and heats of formation for fluorinated ethers: E143A (CF<inf>3</inf>OCH<inf>3</inf>), E134 (CHF<inf>2</inf>OCHF<inf>2</inf>), and E125 (CHF<inf>2</inf>OCF<inf>3</inf>) (1998) J. Phys. Chem., 102, pp. 7143-7148; Good, D.A., Kamboures, M., Santiano, R., Francisco, J.S., Atmospheric oxidation of fluorinated ethers, E143a (CF <inf>3</inf>OCH<inf>3</inf>), E